{"lemma":"صَبْرُ","slug":"صَبْرُ","root":"ص.ب.ر","root_slug":"ص-ب-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ص-ب-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"صَبْر","root":"صبر","pos":"N","occurrence_count":15},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":6,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":18},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n23667","n23668","n23669","n23670","n23671","n23672"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B5%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%92%D8%B1%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be patient, to have patience"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to bind, to tie, to fetter, to shackle"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to persevere, to endure"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to refrain, to abstain, to renounce"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to ask to be patient, to admonish to be patient"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to console, to comfort"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to conserve"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to preserve, to can"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of صَبَرَ (ṣabara) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"fettering, shackling"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"patience, forbearance","examples":[{"text":"الصَّبْرُ مِفْتَاحُ ٱلْفَرَجِ","english":"Patience is the key to deliverance."},{"text":"قَلَّ صَبْرُهُ.","english":"His patience ran out."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"composure, self-control"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"equanimity, steadfastness"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"perseverance, endurance, hardiness"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"ice","tags":["collective"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"aloe"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"bitterness; juice of any bitter plant, aloe, myrrh","tags":["Classical"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to ballast"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Borrowed from Aramaic, found in Jewish Palestinian Aramaic צברה and Classical Syriac ܨܒܪܐ (ṣabrā, ṣabbārā), ܨܘܪܐ (ṣawrā), from Akkadian [script needed] (ṣibaru, ṣiburu, “a pointed gardening instrument; a fleshy excrescence; a plant in medical texts a medication for gall-bladder disease, apparently aloe comparable to the garden-tool by its lanceolate leaves”). For relevant vocalization variants, against the standard Arabic صَبِر (ṣabir, “aloe”) and صَبْر (ṣabr, “aloe”), the Andalusi dialect, which has been reckoned the most conservative of the Middle Arabic ones, used صِبْر (ṣibr) and صِبَر (ṣibar), and صَبَّار (ṣabbār), صُبَّار (ṣubbār, “cactus; nonstandardly and also Andalusi aloe”) is extended from this word.\n\nDenominal verb of صَابُورَة (ṣābūra, “ballast”)."},"ipa":["/sˤa.ba.ra/","/sˤab.ba.ra/","/sˤabr/","/sˤa.bar/","/sˤa.bir/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n23667","headword_ar":"صَبْرٌ","root":"Sbr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[inf. n. of 1, q. v. ―         -b2-  Used as a simple subst.,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Patience,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"endurance; contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jazaEN","text_ar":"جَزَعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"restraint of oneself,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of one's soul, from impatience."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S. [Several other explanations of this word are shown by explanations of the verb.]) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ahoru AlS~abori","text_ar":"شَهْرُ الصَّبْرِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The month of fasting:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) fasting being called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sabor","text_ar":"صَبْر"},{"kind":"text","text":"because it is self-restraint from food and beverage and sexual intercourse. (TA, from a trad.) ―         -b4-  ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qatalahu SaborFA","text_ar":"قَتَلَهُ صَبْرًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qutila SaborFA","text_ar":"قُتِلَ صَبْرًا"},{"kind":"text","text":": see 1.] ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yamiynu AlS~abori","text_ar":"يَمِينُ الصَّبْرِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The oath for which the judge,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"governor,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in the CK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHukomu","text_ar":"الحُكْمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is erroneously put for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHakamu","text_ar":"الحَكَمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":",]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"holds one in custody until he swears it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the oath that is obligatory"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon the swearer,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and which the swearer is compelled to take,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he being confined by the Sultán until he do so:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, * TA:) such an oath is also termed ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yamiynN maSobuwrapN","text_ar":"يَمِينٌ مَصْبُورَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Mgh:) [i. e.] the term"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maSobuwrapN","text_ar":"مَصْبُورَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is applied to an oath, (S, K, TA,) meaning one"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"on account of which a man is confined, in order to make him swear it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA; [and this seems to be indicated by the context in the S and K;]) but the man being"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maSobuwr","text_ar":"مَصْبُور"},{"kind":"text","text":", and not the oath, the latter is thus"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1645},{"kind":"text","text":"termed tropically. (TA.) ―         -b6-  ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Halafa SaborFA","text_ar":"حَلَفَ صَبْرًا"},{"kind":"text","text":": see 1.]       -A2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SabirN","text_ar":"صَبِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["M","K","TA","Mgh","S"]},{"entry_id":"n23668","headword_ar":"صُبْرٌ","root":"Sbr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, Msb, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SiborN","text_ar":"صِبْرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, Msb, K) The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"side"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a thing: (S, M, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a side rising above the rest"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a thing: (Msb:) or its"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upper part,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"top:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"edge"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a thing: (S, M, K:) and its"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thickness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"formed by transposition from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buSorN","text_ar":"بُصْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^FSobaArN","text_ar":"اًصْبَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, Msb, K,) and pl. pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSobaArapN","text_ar":"اَصْبَارَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSobaArN","text_ar":"اَصْبَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sides"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a vessel, (S,) and of a grave. (TA.) And you say, He filled the drinking-cup, (S, M, A, K,) and the measure, (A, TA,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ilaY A^aSobaArihi","text_ar":"اـِلَى اَصْبَارِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, A, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to its top,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K,) as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlY","text_ar":"الى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSomaArihi","text_ar":"اَصْمَارِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to its uppermost parts;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to its edges."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axa*ahu biA^aSobaArihi","text_ar":"اَخَذَهُ بِاَصْبَارِهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He took it altogether."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, A, Msb, * K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laqiYa Al$~id~apa","text_ar":"لَقِىَ الشِّدَّةَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biA^aSobaArihaA","text_ar":"بِاَصْبَارِهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He met with complete distress,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"adversity."},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, S.) And in a trad., the tree called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sidorapu AlmunotahaY","text_ar":"سِدْرَةُ المُنْتَهَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"is said to be"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Subora Aljan~api","text_ar":"صُبْرَ الجَنَّةِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the highest part of Paradise."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA.) ―         -b2-  Also the former, (S, M, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SuburN","text_ar":"صُبُرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Land in which are pebbles,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not rugged."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M.) Hence, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^um~u Sab~aArK","text_ar":"اُمُّ صَبَّارٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v. (S, M.) ―         -b3-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SabiyrN","text_ar":"صَبِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places."}],"source_refs":["S","M","Msb","K","TA","A"]},{"entry_id":"n23669","headword_ar":"صِبْرٌ","root":"Sbr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SuborN","text_ar":"صُبْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": ―         -b2-  and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SabiyrN","text_ar":"صَبِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in two places:       -A2-  and see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SabirN","text_ar":"صَبِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n23670","headword_ar":"صَبَرٌ","root":"Sbr","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Ice;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HamadN","text_ar":"حَمَدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (A, Sgh, K:) and [its n. un.] with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a piece thereof:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, Sgh:) from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSobara","text_ar":"اَصْبَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ai$otad~a","text_ar":"اِشْتَدَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (A.)"}],"source_refs":["A","Sgh","K"]},{"entry_id":"n23671","headword_ar":"صَبِرٌ","root":"Sbr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, Msb, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaborN","text_ar":"صَبْرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", which latter is allowable only in cases of necessity in poetry, (S, Msb, K,) or it is allowable in other cases, as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SiborN","text_ar":"صِبْرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", agreeably with analogy, (Ibn-Es-Seed, Msb,) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Aloes;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain bitter medicine;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, Msb;) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"expressed juice of a certain bitter tree;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K;) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"expressed juice of a certain tree of which the leaves are like the sheaths of knives, long and thick, with a dusty and dull hue in their greenness, of rough appearance, from the midst of which there comes forth a stalk whereon is a yellow flower,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vmd","text_ar":"ثمد"},{"kind":"text","text":"[but what this means I know not]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in odour;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it grows like the green"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suwsan","text_ar":"سُوسَن"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lily"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"save that the leaves of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sbr","text_ar":"صبر"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"are longer and broader and much thicker, and it contains very much juice;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHn, M, O, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it is crushed and thrown into the presses, then bruised with pieces of wood, and trodden with the feet until its expressed juice flows, when it is left until it thickens, then it is put into leathern bags, and exposed to the sun until it dries:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHn, O:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the best sort is the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suquToriY~","text_ar":"سُقُطْرِىّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the Island of Sukutrà"},{"kind":"text","text":"]:"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and it is also known by the name of"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sab~aArapN","text_ar":"صَبَّارَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[a name now applied to the plant]: (TA:) the n. un. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SabirapN","text_ar":"صَبِرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaborapN","text_ar":"صَبْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SiborapN","text_ar":"صِبْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SubuwrN","text_ar":"صُبُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M, TA.) ―         -b2-  [Accord. to Freytag, it signifies also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Myrrh:"},{"kind":"text","text":"but for this I know not any authority.]"}],"source_refs":["S","M","Msb","K","AHn","O","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n23672","headword_ar":"صُبُرٌ","root":"Sbr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SuborN","text_ar":"صُبْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]}]}}